[normal]The past several years of the Israeli-Palestinian conflict has been characterized by an absence and stalling of any political or diplomatic dialogue, therefor the current peace talks make the work on
[normal] the ground
[normal] and
[normal] the 
[normal]p
[normal]eople to 
[normal]p
[normal]eople approach more important than ever. The ongoing conflict continues to create barriers – both emotional and 
[normal]physical
[normal] – between both societies.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The PCFF’s work is based on the premise that reconciliation is a multi – level
[normal] process necessary to complement and drive any future peace agreement.
[normal]The underlying basis of the 
[normal]people to people 
[normal]p
[normal]rogram
[normal]me
[normal] 
[normal]is
[normal] that change results from the interaction of belligerent groups when there is opportunity for increased mutual understanding and
[normal] appreciation. It also 
[normal]works on the premise 
[normal]that following the initial 
[normal]interaction
[normal], partnerships and 
[normal]collaboration
[normal]s
[normal] addressing common concerns create a real long-term commitment, on the way to 
[normal]building 
[normal]true peace between people and communities.
